ECA protects the rights of both local factorybased workers and outworkers (also known as homeworkers). Outworkers are particularly vulnerable in the Textile, Clothing and Footwear industry as they often work in isolation and can be unregulated. They can face unrealistic deadlines, long hours, irregular flows of work and occupational health and safety issues. Other issues include lack of awareness of legal rights and entitlements, and powerlessness to speak out about problems in fear of losing work altogether. Workers in the local industry are predominately women and includes many women from culturally diverse backgrounds and with languages other than English.
